In addition to existing PubMed search results, this extension will add direct PDF link; display F1000 scores, Impact Factor, Peaks and much more...

The enhancement includes: 
* Impact Factor of the Journal 
* Direct link to its PDF file 
* External pages related to the article 
* Faculty 1000 score and link to its comment page
* "Peaks", which is based on Impact Factor (the playground for "Peaks" is at http://paperlink2.appspot.com/static/peaks.html)
* ...

This extension is built using API from http://pubmeder.appspot.com, http://thepaperlink.appspot.com, http://paperlink2.appspot.com and eUtils.


For Firefox, please use the following:
* http://userscripts.org/scripts/show/97865 (need GreaseMonkey, tested with fx4)
* https://addons.mozilla.org/en-US/firefox/addon/thepaperlinkforpubmed/ (not work in 4.0 yet)

For Safari, please use the following:
* http://thepaperlink.appspot.com/static/thepaperlink.safariextz

For Mobile Devices, please try our mobile site:
* http://thepaperlink.appspot.com/m (or visit http://thepaperlink.com on your mobile device: iPhone, Android, iPod Touch, iPad, etc)


There is one more thing - we have a js client for "the Paper Link", working in all web browsers.
* http://thepaperlink.appspot.com/js/ (shorten URL http://goo.gl/m5C49)
* instruction for the js client is at http://en.dogeno.us/?p=7567


Change Log:
* v0.1.1 - first public version
* v0.1.2 - "pubmeder all" for users of "pubmeder at appspot.com"
* v0.2.0 - two-hit for fast data fetching
* v0.2.1 - bug fix
* v0.2.2 - add https support
* v0.2.3 - test using "Peaks" api
* v0.2.4 - option page ui improved, "Peaks" full functional
* v0.2.5 - option page update
* v0.2.6 - better "pubmeder it / pubmeder all" bookmarking
* v0.2.7 - lousy fix json fetch error (update to jQuery 1.5.2)
* v0.2.8 - "email it" will try to download PDF file and attach it (Chrome Only); some UI tweak

Source of this extension is at https://github.com/coronin/thepaperlink-chrome
